==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Salifiable
<hw>Sal"i*fi`a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>salifiable</ets>. See <er>Salify</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Capable of neutralizing an acid to form a salt; -- said of bases;
thus, ammonia is <xex>salifiable</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Salification</ent>⟦br⟧
